cs.IT, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.DM, cs.SI 

The paper introduces a new measure of uncertainty in the Dempster-Shafer theory, which is a framework for reasoning under uncertainty. This makes it likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a new entropy-like measure, which is a common concept in Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Data Mining (cs.DM). Finally, the paper's focus on uncertainty and measures of discord could also make it relevant to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category.
